 <!-- Why Compare Section -->
 <BenefitCards 
 title="Why Compare These Platforms?"
 benefits={whyCompare}
 />

 <!-- Social Proof -->
 <SocialProof 
 title="What Learners Say"
 testimonials={testimonials}
 />

 <!-- Ad Unit -->
 <div class="mb-8">
 <AdUnit slot="compare-1" />
 </div>

 <!-- What Are the Main Differences -->
 <section class="bg-slate-900/60 rounded-xl shadow-lg p-6 mb-8">
 <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-white mb-4">What Are the Main Differences?</h2>
 <p class="text-neutral-300 mb-4 leading-relaxed">Busuu is a structured language learning platform. It provides a complete curriculum, vocabulary, grammar, reading, listening, and speaking, mapped to CEFR levels from A1 to B2. You work through units at your own pace, get AI feedback on writing and pronunciation, and can earn an official certification recognised by McGraw-Hill Education.</p>
 <p class="text-neutral-300 mb-4 leading-relaxed">iTalki is a tutoring marketplace. There is no built-in curriculum, instead, you browse thousands of human tutors, read their profiles, and book live video lessons when it suits you. The learning is entirely conversation-based: you talk, the tutor gives feedback, you talk some more. The pace and content depend on your tutor and your goals.</p>
 <p class="text-neutral-300 leading-relaxed">The fundamental difference is self-study vs live tutoring. Busuu gives you a map and lets you walk it yourself. iTalki puts you in a room with a guide who adapts to your every question and mistake in real time. Both approaches work, the right choice depends on how you learn best and what you are trying to achieve.</p>
 </section>

 <!-- Enhanced Comparison Table -->
 <ComparisonHighlight 
 title="Feature Comparison"
 platformA={busuu}
 platformB={italki}
 winner="b"
 rows={comparison}
 />

 <!-- Ad Unit -->
 <div class="mb-8">
 <AdUnit slot="compare-2" />
 </div>

 <!-- Detailed Analysis -->
 <section class="bg-slate-900/60 rounded-xl shadow-lg p-6 mb-8">
 <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-white mb-6">Detailed Analysis</h2>
 
 <div class="mb-8">
 <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-white mb-3">Learning Structure</h3>
 <h4 class="text-lg font-semibold text-purple-400 mb-2">Busuu: A Clear Path From Beginner to Advanced</h4>
 <p class="text-neutral-300 mb-4 leading-relaxed">Busuu's greatest strength is its structure. The curriculum is mapped to CEFR levels, so you always know exactly where you are and what comes next. Units cover vocabulary, grammar, dialogues, and speaking practice, all designed to build on each other in a logical progression. This makes it easy to study consistently without having to decide what to do next.</p>
 <p class="text-neutral-300 leading-relaxed">The community correction feature is also valuable: native speakers review your written exercises and give feedback. This adds a human element to the self-study experience, making it feel less isolated than some other apps.</p>
 </div>

 <div class="mb-8">
 <h4 class="text-lg font-semibold text-emerald-400 mb-2">iTalki: Flexible, Human-Led Learning</h4>
 <p class="text-neutral-300 mb-4 leading-relaxed">iTalki's learning is as structured, or as unstructured, as you make it. If you want a structured path, you work with a tutor who designs a lesson plan for you. If you prefer free conversation, you just talk. Some learners thrive in this flexibility; others need the guardrails that Busuu provides.</p>
 <p class="text-neutral-300 mb-4 leading-relaxed">The key advantage is human adaptability. Your tutor hears you speak, notices patterns in your mistakes, and explains things in context, something AI cannot replicate. They can answer your specific questions, push you when you are coasting, and slow down when you are struggling. This real-time responsiveness is iTalki's biggest selling point.</p>
 </div>

 <div>
 <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-white mb-3">Speaking Practice</h3>
 <p class="text-neutral-300 mb-4 leading-relaxed">Busuu offers AI-powered speaking practice with speech recognition that gives feedback on your pronunciation. This is genuinely useful for drilling specific sounds and phrases. However, it cannot hold a conversation or respond to what you say in real time.</p>
 <p class="text-neutral-300 mb-4 leading-relaxed">iTalki's speaking practice is conversation with a human being. You talk, they respond, you talk back. This is the fastest way to build real conversational ability because every mistake is caught immediately and every question is answered naturally.</p>
 <p class="text-neutral-300 leading-relaxed">For the best results, use both: Busuu to build vocabulary and study grammar through its structured exercises, then iTalki to put everything into practice in live conversations.</p>
 </div>
 </section>

 <!-- FAQ Section -->
 <section class="bg-slate-900/60 rounded-xl shadow-lg p-6 mb-8">
 <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-white mb-6">Frequently Asked Questions</h2>
 
 <div class="space-y-6">
 <div>
 <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-white mb-2">Is Busuu or iTalki better for learning English?</h3>
 <p class="text-neutral-300">
 <strong>It depends on your goals and learning style.</strong>Busuu is better if you want structured, self-paced learning with a clear curriculum and AI tools for writing and pronunciation practice. iTalki is better if you want to develop real speaking ability through live conversations with human tutors. Many learners use both, Busuu for grammar and vocabulary, iTalki for speaking practice.
 </p>
 </div>

 <div>
 <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-white mb-2">Which is cheaper, Busuu or iTalki?</h3>
 <p class="text-neutral-300">Busuu costs from <strong>$13.99/month</strong>for full access to all courses and features. iTalki lessons start at <strong>$5</strong>with community tutors, but you pay per lesson. If you only need a few lessons per month, iTalki could be cheaper. If you plan to practice daily with structured content, Busuu's subscription may offer better value.
 </p>
 </div>

 <div>
 <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-white mb-2">Can I use both Busuu and iTalki together?</h3>
 <p class="text-neutral-300">
 <strong>Yes, this is actually one of the most effective combinations.</strong>Use Busuu to build vocabulary, grammar, and reading comprehension through its structured curriculum. Book iTalki sessions weekly to practice what you have learned in real conversations. This gives you the best of both worlds: a clear learning path plus human speaking practice.
 </p>
 </div>

 <div>
 <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-white mb-2">Does Busuu have speaking practice?</h3>
 <p class="text-neutral-300">Busuu has AI-powered speaking practice through its speech recognition feature, which gives feedback on pronunciation. However, this is not the same as live conversation. You can practice individual words and phrases, but you cannot hold a spontaneous conversation with the AI. For real conversational ability, <strong>iTalki's live human tutors are significantly more effective</strong>.
 </p>
 </div>

 <div>
 <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-white mb-2">Which platform is better for beginners?</h3>
 <p class="text-neutral-300">
 <strong>Busuu is generally better for beginners</strong>who want a structured, guided path through the fundamentals. Its curriculum spans CEFR A1 to B2 with clear milestones and exercises. iTalki is better for beginners who are comfortable jumping into conversation and want immediate speaking practice from day one, though the lack of structured content means you may not build as solid a foundation in grammar and vocabulary.
 </p>
 </div>
 </div>
 </section>

 <!-- Ad Unit -->
 <div class="mb-8">
 <AdUnit slot="compare-3" />
 </div>

 <!-- Verdict Section -->
 <section class="bg-gradient-to-r from-purple-900/40 to-indigo-900/40 rounded-xl p-6 mb-8">
 <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-white mb-4">Which Should You Choose?</h2>
 <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-6 mb-6">
 <div class="bg-slate-900/60 rounded-lg p-4 border-l-4 border-purple-500">
 <h3 class="font-bold text-neutral-300 mb-2">Choose Busuu if:</h3>
 <ul class="text-neutral-300 space-y-2">
 <li class="flex items-start"><span class="text-purple-500 mr-2">→</span>You prefer structured, self-paced learning</li>
 <li class="flex items-start"><span class="text-purple-500 mr-2">→</span>You want a clear curriculum from A1 to B2</li>
 <li class="flex items-start"><span class="text-purple-500 mr-2">→</span>You need offline access for commuting or travel</li>
 <li class="flex items-start"><span class="text-purple-500 mr-2">→</span>You want an official certification (McGraw-Hill)</li>
 </ul>
 </div>
 <div class="bg-slate-900/60 rounded-lg p-4 border-l-4 border-emerald-500">
 <h3 class="font-bold text-emerald-300 mb-2">Choose iTalki if:</h3>
 <ul class="text-neutral-300 space-y-2">
 <li class="flex items-start"><span class="text-emerald-500 mr-2">→</span>Your main goal is to speak English confidently</li>
 <li class="flex items-start"><span class="text-emerald-500 mr-2">→</span>You want instant feedback from a real human</li>
 <li class="flex items-start"><span class="text-emerald-500 mr-2">→</span>You are preparing for a test, interview, or travel</li>
 <li class="flex items-start"><span class="text-emerald-500 mr-2">→</span>You prefer flexible, conversation-based learning</li>
 </ul>
 </div>
 </div>
 <p class="text-neutral-300">The most effective approach for most learners is to use both: Busuu for structured vocabulary and grammar study, iTalki for weekly conversation practice to apply what you have learned in real dialogues.</p>
 </section>

 <!-- See Guru Alternative -->
 <section class="bg-blue-900/40 border border-blue-700/50 rounded-xl p-6 mb-8">
 <p class="font-bold text-lg mb-2">Try See Guru as an Alternative</p>
 <p class="text-slate-300 mb-4">If you want live tutoring sessions at a fixed monthly price, See Guru is another option worth considering. It offers structured small-group classes and one-on-one tutoring with certified teachers, including three free trial lessons.</p>
